alert.note: Alert for St. Louis (Minnesota) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued April 26 at 8:28PM CDT until April 29 at 4:00AM CDT by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 1130 PM CDT THIS EVENING... * WHAT...Flooding caused by rain and snowmelt is expected. * WHERE...A portion of northeast Minnesota, including the following county, St. Louis. * WHEN...Until 1130 PM CDT. * IMPACTS...Flooding of rivers, creeks, streams, and other low-lying and flood-prone locations is imminent or occurring. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 827 PM CDT, gauge reports and public works reported high water on the Sturgeon River due to recent heavy rain and continued snowmelt. Flooding is ongoing or expected to begin shortly in the warned area. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... mainly rural areas of Northwestern St. Louis County - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
